 "faq": [
  {
   "question": "Where does Marksmanship Hunter Phase 4 BiS come from?",
   "answer": "From the gear worn by 266 top-ranked Marksmanship Hunter DPS parses on Warcraft Logs during Phase 4 (Zul'Aman), aggregated per slot — what high parsers actually equip, not a spreadsheet ideal."
  },
  {
   "question": "What are the highest-consensus Marksmanship Hunter items in Phase 4?",
   "answer": "Gronnstalker's Gloves (92%), Gronnstalker's Spaulders (83%), Gronnstalker's Chestguard (80%). When an item sits above ~70% among top parsers, treat it as the priority drop to chase."
  },
  {
   "question": "Should I follow this list exactly for Phase 4?",
   "answer": "Use it as a loot-priority guide, not a checklist — expand each slot's alternatives, because second-choice items are often within a few percent and drop from entirely different bosses in Zul'Aman."
  },
  {
   "question": "What gems should a Marksmanship Hunter use in Phase 4?",
   "answer": "Relentless Earthstorm Diamond in the meta socket, then Delicate Living Ruby, Wicked Flame Spessarite and Shifting Nightseye in the coloured sockets. Epic gems only arrive with patch 2.4 (Sunwell), so these rare-quality cuts are the ceiling for this phase."
  },
  {
   "question": "What enchants does a Marksmanship Hunter need in Phase 4?",
   "answer": "11 slots are worth enchanting. The biggest swings are Glyph of Ferocity on head, Might of the Scourge on shoulders, Nethercobra Leg Armor on legs and Enchant Weapon - Greater Agility on weapon. The head and shoulder enchants are consumable items rather than enchanter work — Glyph of Ferocity comes from Fedryen Swiftwpear — Zangarmarsh."
  }
 ]
